-- Westar to Buy 200 Megawatts of Energy From Oklahoma Wind Project
-- B y   J u s t i n   D o o m
-- 2013-11-06T22:03:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-06/westar-to-buy-200-megawatts-of-energy-from-oklahoma-wind-project.html
Westar Energy Inc. (WR) , the largest
electricity provider in Kansas, agreed to buy 200 megawatts of
capacity from a wind farm that Apex Clean Energy Inc. is
developing in northern Oklahoma.  Construction on the project 6 miles (9.7 kilometers) south
of Arkansas City, Kansas, is expected to begin in 2015 and the
wind farm will be operational the following year, Topeka,
Kansas-based Westar said in a statement today. Terms werenâ€™t
